x4codes.hlp: Off-line mass separation of a product

x4freetext: On-line mass separation of fission products
detected with a silicon surface barrier detector at
the exit slit of the spectrometer, mass resolving
.Nuclear charge distributions for each mass chain
are measured with a time of flight technique after
fission product energy loss in a thin homogeneous
carbon absorber foil. The time of flight spectra
are unfolded to give fractional independent yields
as a function of the fragment kinetic energies.
Solid state silicon surface barrier detector
for energy measurement and as a stop signal for time
.The data were corrected for the mass and energy
.All nuclear charge distributions have been corrected
for multiple scattering in the carbon absorber.
.Correction of the yields for source thickness and
.All mass and charge yields have been corrected for
the influence of the ionic charge distribution.
